📌 What is Amazon RDS?
            Amazon RDS (Relational Database Service) is a fully managed AWS service that makes it easy to set up, 
            operate, and scale a relational database in the cloud. AWS handles all the heavy lifting 
            — backups, patching, scaling, and high availability.
🗄️ Part 1 — Create the Database:
            Step 1 — Navigate:
                        Go to AWS Console → Search "RDS" → Click "RDS"
                        In the left panel → Click "Databases"
                        Click "Create Database" ✅
            Step 2 — Choose Database Creation Method:
                        Setting	            Value
                        Creation Method	Standard Create(Full Configuration)
                        ⚠️ Correction: You said "Aurora RDS" but then selected MySQL with Free Tier. Amazon Aurora is NOT available on Free Tier. 
                        Select MySQL engine directly — not Aurora. Aurora costs money even at minimal usage.
            Step 3 — Engine Selection:
                        Setting	            Value
                        Engine Type	            MySQL
                        Edition	            MySQL Community
                        Engine Version	MySQL 8.0 (latest stable)
            Step 4 — Template:
                        Setting	Value
                        Template	Free Tier ✅
                                  
            Step 5 — Settings / Credentials:
                        Setting	            Value
                        DB Instance Identifier	database-1
                        Master Username	admin
                        Credential Management	Self Managed
                        Master Password	admin123
                        Confirm Password	admin123
                        ⚠️ Security Note:admin123 is fine for learning/demo purposes. For production — always use a strong password with uppercase, numbers and special characters.
            
            Step 6 — Instance Configuration:
                        Setting	            Value
                        DB Instance Class	db.t3.micro(auto-set by Free Tier)
                        Storage Type	gp2(General Purpose SSD)
                        Allocated Storage	20 GB
                        Storage Autoscaling	Leave as default
            Step 7 — Connectivity:
                        Setting	            Value
                        Compute Resource	Don't connect to EC2
                        VPC	            Default VPC
                        Subnet Group	Default
                        Publicly Accessible	YES ✅
                        Availability Zone	No preference (Free Tier)
                        VPC Security Group	Create New
                        Security Group Name	demo-rds-sg
                        Port	3306
            Step 8 — Additional Configuration:
                        Expand "Additional Configuration" section
                        Configure:
                        Setting	            Value
                        Initial Database Name	myDb
                        Automated Backups	Leave as default
                        Encryption	Leave as default
                        Maintenance	Leave as default
                        ⚠️ If you skip Initial Database Name — AWS will create the RDS instance but no database will exist inside it. You would have to create it manually via SQL later.
