🔐 Part 2 — Fix Security Group (Allow External Access):
            Step 1 — Get the Endpoint:
                        Go to RDS → Databases → Select database-1
                        Click "Connectivity & Security" tab
                        Click the "Endpoint" radio button / tab
                        Copy the Endpoint DNS name:
                        database-1.clsc646wqidu.ap-south-1.rds.amazonaws.com
            Step 2 — Edit Security Group Inbound Rules:
                        In the Connectivity & Security tab
                        Under Security Groups → Click demo-rds-sg(opens new tab)
                        Click "Inbound Rules" → "Edit Inbound Rules"
                        You will see an existing rule — delete it and add a new one:
                        Setting	            Value
                        Type	            MySQL/Aurora
                        Protocol	            TCP
                        Port	            3306
                        Source	            Anywhere - IPv4 (0.0.0.0/0)
                        Click "Save Rules" ✅
                        Before Fix:
                        Your PC (152.59.x.x) ──→ RDS SG ──→ ❌ BLOCKED
            
                        After Fix:
                        Your PC (152.59.x.x) ──→ RDS SG ──→ ✅ Port 3306 OPEN
                                                            ──→ RDS MySQL ✅
                        ⚠️ Security Note:0.0.0.0/0 (Anywhere) is fine for learning/demo. For production — always restrict to your specific IP or your app server's IP only.
                        
